
Utility Scripts for various repetitive tasks
============================================

CPU UTILITIES
-------------
cpucount	: number of cpu cores in the system
cpumodel	: model and speed of the system cpus
cpusockets	: number of cpu sockets on the MB
cpuspeed	: cpu speed in Hz
cputop		: similar to lscpu, but slightly different info
cpuxspeed	: set the cpu speed parameters

DISK TOOLS
----------
blocksize	: prints the blocksize of a block device, e.g. /dev/sda
distro2iso	: write a distro tree to a bootable iso file
duh		: du -hs on current or optional other directory
findblockdev	: locates all the block devices in the system
getuuids	: prints all uuids in system

ENVIRONMENT INIT
----------------
ark2host	: initializes a system with my environment
delete-my-stuff	: delete my environment from a system
getsystem	: captures basic system info

GIT UTILITIES
-------------
extup		: extracts upstream commits from a range of rhel commits
gitamselect	: selectively applies patch files in a directory
git-backport	: prarit's git backporting script


GRUB UTILITIES
--------------
g2-envlist	: executes grub2-editenv list
g2-list		: list the menu entries in the grub menu
g2-mkconfig	: executes grub2-mkconfig -o <output-file-spec>
g2-setdef	: executes grub2-set-default to the menu expression

LOG NAVIGATORS
--------------
acpi-ipmi-msg	: greps dmesg for acpi and ipmi messages
bldlog		: greps make.log (output of kmake) for errors and warnings

MISC UTILITIES
--------------
blacklist	: blacklists a driver
braceprofiler	: prints { and } with line numbers to help locate any missing
chkbit		: determines if a bit is set in the mask argument
create-load	: load the system moving zeroes from /dev/zero to /dev/null
diffdir		: diff matching files in two dirs and print files that diff
dmitop		: extract basic hw and fw info from demidecode
entropy		: creates system entropy
fixup-rsync	: useful for chmod to owner after rsync
foreachfile	: executes commands on a file specification
getbit.cpp	: getbit bit-number mask returns 1 if bit-number is set in mask

PATCHTOOLS
----------
cherp		: git cherry-picking tool
dpat		: compare $1 with the patch in ../pat directory
getarkpatch	: downloads patches from post-office.corp.redhat.com
getpatchwork	: downloads patches from patchwork.lab.bos.redhat.com

SEARCH TOOLS
------------
braceprofiler	: prints { and } with line numbers to help locate any missing
findinclude	: recursively search sources for a nested include file
findtil		: Copies files named ??????~?.jpg into a destination dir
getallinclude	: searches dir tree for #include. Called by findinclude
getinclude	: extracts filename including any path info from $include decl
		: : called by findinclude

SCRIPTING TOOLS
---------------
createoptions	: create an options parser template
getyn		: prints prompt and gets yes or no from user

TESTS
-----
bootloop	: puts the system in a user controllable boot loop

TEXT MANIPULATION
-----------------
deleteline	: delete line containing string $1 in file $2
deletelinen	: delete a 1-based line $1 from file $2



